  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Normal vision (also called emmetropia) is the condition in which the eye
    focuses light perfectly onto the retina, allowing a person to see objects clearly
    at all distances without needing glasses or contact lenses.


    Visual Acuity
    (20/20 Vision):

    Many people think normal vision means 20/20 vision, but
    that''s only one measure.

    20/20 vision means:

    At 20 feet (6 meters),
    you can see what a person with standard vision should see at that distance.


    Accommodation:

    The
    eye can automatically change focus for objects at different distances.

    For
    near objects:

    1. Ciliary muscles contract.

    2. Lens becomes thicker.

    For
    distant objects:

    1. Ciliary muscles relax.

    2. Lens becomes thinner.

    This
    process is called accommodation.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
