  m_text: '1. Regular eye checkups: Early detection helps ensure appropriate correction.

    2.
    Use proper lighting: Adequate lighting reduces eye strain during reading and
    close work.

    3. Take frequent visual breaks: Resting the eyes helps reduce
    fatigue.

    4. Maintain a healthy diet: Nutrient-rich foods support overall
    eye health.

    5. Follow good reading habits: Keep reading materials at a comfortable
    distance.

    6. Limit prolonged screen use: Taking breaks can reduce eye discomfort.

    7.
    Get sufficient sleep: Proper rest helps maintain eye comfort and function.

    8.
    Wear prescribed corrective lenses: Using the correct glasses or contact lenses
    improves daily visual performance.'
