  m_text: '1. Regular eye checkups: Early detection helps prevent complications and
    ensures proper treatment.

    2. Proper lighting: Reading and working in adequate
    light reduce eye strain.

    3. Take visual breaks: Follow the 20-20-20 rule
    during prolonged near work.

    4. Maintain a healthy lifestyle: Eat nutritious
    foods rich in vitamins A, C, and E to support eye health.

    5. Limit excessive
    screen time: Reducing continuous screen use helps decrease eye fatigue.

    6.
    Get adequate sleep: Proper rest allows the eye muscles to recover and function
    efficiently.

    7. Use prescribed corrective lenses: Wearing the correct glasses
    or contact lenses improves vision and comfort.

    8. Maintain proper reading
    distance: Keeping books and screens at a suitable distance helps reduce eye strain.'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
