  m_text: '1. Genetic inheritance: The most common cause, passed from parents to
    children.

    2. Defective or missing cone cells: One or more types of color-detecting
    cones in the retina may not function properly.

    3. Eye diseases: Conditions
    affecting the retina or optic nerve can lead to color vision deficiency.

    4.
    Aging: Color perception may decline with age.

    5. Eye injuries: Damage to
    the eye or visual pathways can affect color vision.

    6. Certain medications:
    Some drugs may alter the ability to distinguish colors.'
